call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Garland (CLE) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to the Jazz.
LeVert (CLE) jumps to contest the shot attempt by Clarkson (UTA) and turns away from his body and marginal contact occurs after the release of his shot.
Stevens (CLE) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds. The Jazz retains the possession.

Levert (CLE) steps into Clarkson's (UTA) landing area and is called for the foul.  After communicating with the REplay Center, the fouls is deemed a flagrant foul-penalty (1).  All Flagrant Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Kessler (UTA) establishes himself in LeVert's (CLE) path and his legs remain within the frame of his body as contact occurs, which he does not deliver.

LeVert (CLE) takes a step in Clarkson's (UTA) path and initiates body contact which affects his jump shot attempt. Replay review of the foul called on Levert (CLE) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.
Stevens (CLE) establishes himself in Beasley's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Mobley (CLE) slightly extends both hands to Clarkson's (UTA) front and marginal contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Stevens (CLE) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and does not deliver illegal contact to Beasley (UTA) during the pick.
Kessler (UTA) makes clean contact with the ball prior to incidental contact occurring with Stevens (CLE) as both players are in pursuit of the rebound.
Mitchell (CLE) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to the Jazz.
Stevens (CLE) commits a take foul on Beasley (UTA).
Alexander-Walker (UTA) moves slightly into Mitchell's (CLE) space and avoids making arm contact with Mitchell during his jump shot attempt.
Markkanen (UTA) brings his arm toward Garland's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs during Garland's drive.
Mobley (CLE) commits take a foul on Markkanen (UTA).
Mitchell (CLE) is the last player to make contact with the ball before the ball goes out of bounds. The Jazz retains possession.
Mitchell (CLE) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Clarkson (UTA) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Mobley (CLE) commits a take foul on Alexander-Walker (UTA).
